Creating calculated fields 10


1. Under Data pane, Click on the down arrow and select the option Create Calculated Field.


2. Give the title for each calculated field and corresponding calculations and create the following fields.


1. Avg Order Price = SUM ([Total Price])/MAX([Order Id])

2. Avg Orders By Day = SUM([Quantity])/COUNTD(DATE([Order Date]))

3. Avg Pizza Price = SUM([Total Price]) / SUM([Quantity])

4. Avg Pizzas Per Order = SUM([Quantity]) / MAX ([Order Id])

5. Orders Per Day = SUM ([Quantity]) / COUNTD ([Order Date])

6. Sales Per Day = SUM ([Total Price]) / COUNTD ([Order Date])

7. Current Month Sales = IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))}= MONTH([Order Date]) THEN [Total Price]

 END

8. Prev Month Sales = IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))-1}= MONTH([Order Date]) THEN [Total 0 Price]

 END

9. Sales MoM = (sum([Current Month Sales]) - sum([Prev Month Sales]))

 /sum([Prev Month Sales])

10. Current Month Orders = IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))}= MONTH([Order Date]) THEN [Quantity]

 END

11. Prev Month Orders = IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))-1}= MONTH([Order Date]) THEN [Quantity]

 END

12. Orders MoM = (sum([Current Month Orders]) - sum([Prev Month Orders]))

 /sum([Prev Month Orders])

13. Current Month Avg Price = AVG(IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))} = MONTH([Order Date]) THEN([Total Price])

 END)

14. Prev Month Avg Price = AVG(IF {MAX(MONTH([Pick Date]))-1}= MONTH([Order Date]) THEN [Total Price]

 END)

15. Avg Price MoM = ([Current Month Avg Price] - [Prev Month Avg Price])/ ([Prev Month Avg Price])

16. Sales KPI Indicator UP = IF [Sales MoM %]> 0 THEN '?' End

17. Sales KPI Indicatoe DOWN = IF [Sales MoM %]< 0 THEN '?' End

18. Total Orders KPI Indicator UP = IF [Orders MoM %]> 0 THEN '?' END

19. Total Orders KPI Indicator DOWN = IF [Orders MoM %]< 0 THEN '?' End

20. Avg price KPI Indicator UP = IF [Avg Price MoM %]> 0 THEN '?' END

21. Avg Price KPI Indicator DOWN = IF [Avg Price MoM %]< 0 THEN '?' End

22. Avg Hours Monthly Legend = IF [Avg Orders By Day]> 165 THEN "High"

 ELSEIF [Avg Orders By Day] > 135 AND [Avg Orders By Day] <= 165 THEN "Avg"

 ELSEIF [Avg Orders By Day] <= 135 THEN "Low"

 END 

23. Avg Orders Hourly Legend = IF [Avg Orders By Day]> 16 THEN "High"

 ELSEIF [Avg Orders By Day] >8 AND [Avg Orders By Day] <= 16 THEN "Avg"

 ELSEIF [Avg Orders By Day] <=8 THEN "Low"

 END

24. Cell Background = 1
